# NorDug Presentation - Content Sync

## Three Content Sources

| File | Purpose | Format |
|------|---------|--------|
| **index.html** | Slide content shown to audience | HTML, concise bullets |
| **speaker-notes.md** | Full narrative for presenter | Markdown, `## [SLIDE N] Title` sections |
| **topic-bullets.md** | Quick reference / cheat sheet | Markdown, condensed bullets |

## Sync Rule

When changing slide content (facts, numbers, bullets), update **all three** files.

- **speaker-notes.md** = source of truth for full wording
- **index.html** = condensed for display (short bullets, stats)
- **topic-bullets.md** = one-line summary per slide

## Example

Changing "35 servers" to "27 servers" after scope reduction:

1. **index.html**: Update stat `<span class="stat-num">27</span>`
2. **speaker-notes.md**: Update "27 servers" in the [SLIDE 23] section
3. **topic-bullets.md**: Update "27 servers" in [SLIDE 23] Project Scale

## Speaker Notes Format

```markdown
## [SLIDE N] Title
Full narrative text...
*[Click to advance]*
```

## Topic Bullets Format

```markdown
## [SLIDE N] Title
- Bullet 1
- Bullet 2
```
